# Go Testing Patterns

## Test Naming Convention

```
Test{TypeName}_{MethodName}_{Scenario}
```

Examples:
```go
TestTodoService_GetTodoByID_Success
TestTodoService_GetTodoByID_NotFound
TestTodoService_CreateTodo_RepoError
TestTodoHandler_CreateTodo_InvalidPayload
TestTodoDomain_IsValid_EmptyTitle
```

## Standard Test Structure (AAA Pattern)

```go
func TestTodoService_GetTodoByID_Success(t *testing.T) {
    // Arrange
    ctrl := gomock.NewController(t)
    defer ctrl.Finish()

    mockRepo := mocks.NewMockRepository(ctrl)
    mockTodoRepo := mocks.NewMockTodo(ctrl)
    svc := todo.NewService(cfg, log, mockRepo, mockCache)

    expectedTodo := &domain.Todo{ID: "01JXYZ", Title: "Write tests"}
    mockRepo.EXPECT().GetTodoRepository().Return(mockTodoRepo)
    mockTodoRepo.EXPECT().GetTodoByID(gomock.Any(), "01JXYZ").Return(expectedTodo, nil)

    // Act
    result, err := svc.GetTodoByID(context.Background(), "01JXYZ")

    // Assert
    require.NoError(t, err)
    assert.Equal(t, expectedTodo, result)
}
```

## Table-Driven Tests

Use for methods with multiple scenarios sharing the same structure. Use `scenario` for the subtest name and `scenarioDescription` for documentation:

```go
func TestService_Login(t *testing.T) {
    tests := []struct {
        scenario            string
        scenarioDescription string
        email               string
        password            string
        setup               func(*mocks_outbound.MockRepository, *mocks_outbound_repositories.MockUser)
        wantErr             bool
        wantFailure         *fail.Failure
        wantMsg             string
    }{
        {
            scenario:            "success",
            scenarioDescription: "Valid credentials, active user; returns access and refresh tokens.",
            email:               "user@example.com",
            password:            validPassword,
            setup: func(repo *mocks_outbound.MockRepository, userRepo *mocks_outbound_repositories.MockUser) {
                repo.EXPECT().GetUserRepository().Return(userRepo).Times(1)
                userRepo.EXPECT().GetUserByEmail(gomock.Any(), "user@example.com").Return(user, nil).Times(1)
                userRepo.EXPECT().UpdateUser(gomock.Any(), gomock.Any()).Return(nil).Times(1)
            },
            wantErr: false,
        },
        {
            scenario:            "user not found",
            scenarioDescription: "Email does not exist in DB; GetUserByEmail returns ErrNotFound.",
            email:               "nonexistent@example.com",
            password:            "any",
            setup: func(repo *mocks_outbound.MockRepository, userRepo *mocks_outbound_repositories.MockUser) {
                repo.EXPECT().GetUserRepository().Return(userRepo).Times(1)
                userRepo.EXPECT().GetUserByEmail(gomock.Any(), "nonexistent@example.com").
                    Return(nil, fail.New("user not found").WithFailure(fail.ErrNotFound)).Times(1)
            },
            wantErr:     true,
            wantFailure: fail.ErrUnauthorized,
            wantMsg:     "invalid credentials",
        },
        {
            scenario:            "repo error",
            scenarioDescription: "GetUserByEmail returns a non-NotFound error; error is propagated.",
            email:               "user@example.com",
            password:            "any",
            setup: func(repo *mocks_outbound.MockRepository, userRepo *mocks_outbound_repositories.MockUser) {
                repo.EXPECT().GetUserRepository().Return(userRepo).Times(1)
                userRepo.EXPECT().GetUserByEmail(gomock.Any(), "user@example.com").
                    Return(nil, errors.New("database connection failed")).Times(1)
            },
            wantErr:     true,
            wantFailure: fail.ErrInternalServer,
            wantMsg:     "database connection failed",
        },
    }

    for _, tt := range tests {
        t.Run(tt.scenario, func(t *testing.T) {
            ctrl := gomock.NewController(t)
            defer ctrl.Finish()

            mockRepo := mocks_outbound.NewMockRepository(ctrl)
            mockUserRepo := mocks_outbound_repositories.NewMockUser(ctrl)
            mockBo := mocks_outbound.NewMockBackoffice(ctrl)
            mockMailer := mocks_outbound.NewMockMailer(ctrl)

            tt.setup(mockRepo, mockUserRepo)

            cfg := authTestConfig()
            log := logger.New("test", logger.Options{})
            svc := NewService(cfg, log, mockRepo, mockBo, mockMailer)

            result, err := svc.Login(context.Background(), tt.email, tt.password)

            if tt.wantErr {
                require.Error(t, err)
                assert.Nil(t, result)
                if tt.wantFailure != nil {
                    assert.True(t, fail.IsFailure(err, tt.wantFailure))
                }
                if tt.wantMsg != "" {
                    assert.Contains(t, err.Error(), tt.wantMsg)
                }
                return
            }

            require.NoError(t, err)
            require.NotNil(t, result)
            assert.NotEmpty(t, result.AccessToken)
            assert.NotEmpty(t, result.RefreshToken)
        })
    }
}
```

### Table-Driven Test Struct Fields

| Field | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `scenario` | Short name for `t.Run(tt.scenario, ...)` |
| `scenarioDescription` | Documents the scenario for maintainability |
| Input fields | Method args (e.g. `email`, `password`, `id`) |
| `setup` | Configures mocks; receives typed mock pointers |
| `wantErr` | When true, expect an error |
| `wantFailure` | Optional; assert `fail.IsFailure(err, tt.wantFailure)` when using komon/fail |
| `wantMsg` | Optional; assert `assert.Contains(t, err.Error(), tt.wantMsg)` |
| `wantX` | Optional success assertions (e.g. `wantTodo`, `wantStatus`) |

## Required Imports for Tests

```go
import (
    "context"
    "errors"
    "testing"

    "github.com/stretchr/testify/assert"
    "github.com/stretchr/testify/require"
    "go.uber.org/mock/gomock"

    "github.com/redhajuanda/komon/fail"

    mocks_outbound "github.com/capioteknologi/kitakaya-agent-be/internal/mocks/outbound"
    mocks_outbound_repositories "github.com/capioteknologi/kitakaya-agent-be/internal/mocks/outbound/repositories"
)
```

## Mock Setup Rules

- Use `gomock.Any()` for context parameters (OpenTelemetry wraps contexts)
- Use `gomock.InOrder(...)` when call order matters
- Use `.Times(n)` or `.AnyTimes()` explicitly when a mock is called multiple times
- Prefer `require.NoError` over `assert.NoError` when subsequent assertions depend on no error

## HTTP Handler Tests (Fiber)

```go
func TestTodoHandler_CreateTodo_Success(t *testing.T) {
    ctrl := gomock.NewController(t)
    defer ctrl.Finish()

    mockSvc := inboundmocks.NewMockTodo(ctrl)
    handler := http.NewHandler(mockSvc)
    app := fiber.New()
    app.Post("/todos", handler.CreateTodo)

    mockSvc.EXPECT().CreateTodo(gomock.Any(), gomock.Any()).Return(nil)

    body := `{"title":"Write tests","description":"important"}`
    req := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodPost, "/todos", strings.NewReader(body))
    req.Header.Set("Content-Type", "application/json")

    resp, err := app.Test(req)
    require.NoError(t, err)
    assert.Equal(t, fiber.StatusCreated, resp.StatusCode)
}
```

## Build Tags

- Unit tests (service, domain): no build tag needed, run with `make test`
- Integration tests (repository/DB): use `//go:build integration` and run with `make test-integration`

```go
//go:build integration

package mariadb_test
```

## Helpers

- Use `t.Helper()` in shared test helpers to get accurate failure line numbers
- Use `t.Cleanup(func() { ... })` instead of `defer` in test helpers
- Prefer `context.Background()` in tests; only use real timeouts when testing timeout behavior

## What AI Must Generate

When asked to implement a method or feature:
1. Generate the `_test.go` file alongside the implementation file
2. Include at minimum: happy path + at least one error path
3. Use table-driven tests when there are 3+ scenarios
4. Use `scenario` and `scenarioDescription` in table-driven structs for clarity
5. For error cases, use `wantErr`, `wantFailure` (komon/fail), and `wantMsg` when applicable
6. Use mockgen-generated mocks from `internal/mocks/outbound/` and `internal/mocks/inbound/`
7. Always import `testify/require` and `testify/assert`
